  {"t":"lead","html":"Palermo is one of the world's great street-food cities — arancine, pane e panelle, sfincione, the famous spleen sandwich, all sold from carts and market stalls that have barely changed the recipe in a century. Wrap that in Arab-Norman history dense enough to earn its own UNESCO listing, and you've got one of Europe's most underrated city breaks."},
